The above was written yesterday.—To my great delight, a berry which I had placed on my table the night before has ripened fully, and by taking it into my hand it spontaneously separated into two or three pieces along the dissepiments. Each cell is easily separable, consisting of a soft mealy fleshy paren- chyma, pinkisl1-white; the outer margin coated with a thin membrane (which forms the outside of the berry); the inner margin (that which looked toward the axis) oblique above and straight underneath; sides with obliquely-ascending furrows.
